section.section:
A request for a medical parole under this section may be filed with the Maryland Parole Commission by:
the inmate seeking the medical parole;
an attorney;
a prison official or employee;
a medical professional;
a family member; or
any other person.

text.section:
The information to be considered by the Commission before granting medical parole shall, at a minimum, include:
the inmate's medical information, including:
a description of the inmate's condition, disease, or syndrome;
a prognosis concerning the likelihood of recovery from the condition, disease, or syndrome;
a description of the inmate's physical incapacity and score on the Karnofsky Performance Scale Index or similar classification of physical impairment; and
a mental health evaluation, where relevant;
discharge information, including:
availability of treatment or professional services within the community;
family support within the community; and
housing availability, including hospital or hospice care; and
case management information, including:
the circumstances of the current offense;
institutional history;
pending charges, sentences and other jurisdictions, and any other detainers; and
criminal history information.
